Vellezzo Bellini is a "comune" (municipality) in the Province of Pavia in the Italian region Lombardy, located about 25 km south of Milan and about 10 km northwest of Pavia. As of 31 December 2004, it had a population of 2,565 and an area of 7.9 km².
Vellezzo Bellini borders the following municipalities: Battuda, Certosa di Pavia, Giussago, Marcignago, Rognano.
